      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 11: These rules grant the active desktop user raw HID read/write access to every hidraw interface from each listed vendor, not just devices/interfaces that Jami has verified as HID Telephony. Vendor-wide hidraw access is broader than needed and can expose unrelated HID interfaces from the same vendor to user-space reads/writes. Please narrow the match to known telephony products/interfaces where possible, or add per-product rules for the supported/tested devices instead of granting all devices from the vendor. For example:\n```suggestion\n# Poly Sync 60-M\nKERNEL\u003d\u003d\"hidraw*\", SUBSYSTEM\u003d\u003d\"hidraw\", ATTRS{idVendor}\u003d\u003d\"047f\", ATTRS{idProduct}\u003d\u003d\"\u003cproduct-id\u003e\", TAG+\u003d\"uaccess\"\n```",
